# .env (dev) and any real secret files must never end up baked into the image —
# app.py's load_dotenv(..., override=True) would let a locally-checked-out
# dev .env silently override the real env_file:-injected production secrets
# at container runtime. The image needs zero .env* files: env_file: in
# docker-compose.*.yml already injects real environment variables directly.
.env
.env.*
!.env*.example

__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
venv/
instance/
*.db
*.sqlite3
